    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI wrote a [skeleton package](https://github.com/GjjvdBurg/NumPy_C_Extension) that links a C library to Python using Cython and NumPy. Compilation worked fine for Cython version 0.27.3 but doesn't work anymore for version 0.28.x. I posted this issue [on StackOverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/q/51099630/) and it was suggested that this might be a problem with Cython, so I'm reporting it here. Steps to reproduce are in the SO post, but to reiterate:\r\n\r\n### 0.27.3 Environment\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nvirtualenv -p python3.6 old\r\ncd old\r\nsource bin/activate\r\npip install cython==0.27.3 numpy==1.13.3\r\ngit clone https://github.com/GjjvdBurg/NumPy_C_Extension\r\ncd NumPy_C_Extension\r\nrm src/cython_wrapper.c\r\npython setup.py build_ext -i\r\n# Compilation proceeds without errors\r\n```\r\n\r\n### 0.28.3 Environment\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nvirtualenv -p python3.6 new\r\ncd new\r\nsource bin/activate\r\npip install cython==0.28.3 numpy==1.14.5\r\ngit clone https://github.com/GjjvdBurg/NumPy_C_Extension\r\ncd NumPy_C_Extension\r\nrm src/cython_wrapper.c\r\npython setup.py build_ext -i\r\n# Compilation fails\r\n```\r\n\r\nThanks for your time!",
    "closed_at": null,
