            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Here is a quite small reproducer for the issue, in the format used by the test suite:\r\n\r\n```\r\nPYTHON setup.py build_ext -i\r\n\r\n######## setup.py ########\r\n\r\nfrom setuptools import setup\r\nfrom numpy.distutils.misc_util import Configuration\r\nfrom Cython.Build import cythonize\r\n\r\nconfig = Configuration('numpy_c_skeleton', '', None)\r\nconfig.add_extension('cython_wrapper', ['src/cython_wrapper.pyx'])\r\nconfig.ext_modules = cythonize(config.ext_modules)\r\nattr = config.todict()\r\nsetup(**attr)\r\n\r\n\r\n######## src/cython_wrapper.pyx ########\r\n\r\n#cimport cython_wrapper\r\n\r\ncdef void do_nothing():\r\n    nothing()\r\n\r\n####### src/helper.h ##########\r\nvoid nothing(){;}\r\n\r\n######## src/cython_wrapper.pxd ########\r\ncdef extern from \"helper.h\":\r\n   void nothing()\r\n\r\ncdef void do_nothing()\r\n\r\n####### numpy_c_skeleton/dummy.txt #########\r\n```\r\nThe error is \"undeclared name not builtin: nothing\" but when we uncomment  `cimport cython_wrapper` in the pyx-file we see, that cython_wrapper.pxd cannot be found. The cython looks for `numpy_c_skeleton/cython_wrapper.pxd` instead of `src/cython_wrapper.pxd`\r\n\r\nThe behavior was changed with the commit:\r\n\r\n> commit f17ece062fb45e63f2fa56d857e1b72e58131482\r\n> Author: Stefan Behnel <stefan_ml@behnel.de>\r\n> Date:   Fri Dec 15 20:19:36 2017 +0100\r\n> \r\n>     Allow overriding the extension module name in cythonize() by setting an explicit name in the Extension() object.\r\n>     Closes #2038.\r\n\r\nTo me it looks like a regression, but I don't know enough to be sure. @scoder is probably the one to ask.\r\n",
